      <div xml:id="NA120-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu viruntu vāyilākap pukka talaivaṉ (ET: talaimakaṉ) colliyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is what HE said who had entered, [wishing for] a feast as a mediator.</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA120">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            taṭamarup perumai maṭanaṭaik kuḻavi</l>
<l>            tūṇṭoṟum yātta kāṇṭaku nalliṟ</l>
<l>            koṭuṅkuḻai peyta ceḻuñcey pēḻai</l>
<l>            ciṟutāḻ ceṟitta melviral cēppa</l>
<l>            vāḻai yīrntaṭi vallitiṉ vakaiip </l>
<l>            pukaiyuṇ ṭamartta kaṇṇa ṭakaipeṟap</l>
<l>            piṟainutaṟ poṟitta ciṟunuṇ palviya</l>
<l>            rantukiṟ ṟalaiyiṟ ṟuṭaiyiṉa ṇappulan</l>
<l>            taṭṭi lōḷē yammā varivai</l>
<l>            yemakkē, varukatil viruntē civappā ḷaṉṟu </l>
<l>            ciṟiya muḷḷeyiṟu tōṉṟa</l>
<l>            muṟuval koṇṭa mukaṅkāṇ kammē.</l>
    </lg>
       <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>That dark young woman, she [is] in the kitchen,<note place="foot">Syntax and impact of lines 3-9 are not at all clear and, as usual, under-marked.</note></l>
<l rend="indent">being vexed with us, she who wiped off with the top of [her] pretty cloth</l>
<l rend="indent">the perspiration in many minute [drops], impressed on her crescent</l>
<l rend="indent3">forehead befittingly(?),</l>
<l rend="indent">she with eyes at strife with the touch of smoke,</l>
<l rend="indent">distributing skilfully(?) the moist flesh on plantain leaves,</l>
<l rend="indent2">so that [her] soft finger become red, on which small rings(?) were tight,</l>
<l rend="indent2">from a richly made(?!) box into which [she] put curved earrings,</l>
<l rend="indent3">in the good house fit to be seen, where to every pillar is bound</l>
<l rend="indent3">a calf with inexperienced gait of the broad-horned buffalo cow.</l>
<l>As for us<note place="foot">T.V.G. wants to read the <term xml:lang="ta">emakkē</term> here as a dative instead of the locative. But it is just as well possible to understand something like "as far as we are concerned".</note>, may a feast come.</l>
<l>May we see [her] face that has taken up a smile</l>
<l rend="indent2">so that [her] thorn teeth appear a little without her being angered.</l>
        </lg>
